parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive frame flex and failure can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially catastrophic consequences, including damage to the vehicle and harm to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: screws working their way out of wood flooring
screws pushing up underneath the linoleum
partition between wet bay and storage bay bending
front driver side jack not straight
board failure under the main bed
pinched decals on the exterior of the nose cap
pin box sinking into nose cap
hairline cracks in the frame/axle hanger
and storage compartment doors opening while towing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Underrated suspension and axle issues can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially catastrophic consequences, including damage to the vehicle and harm to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: and detached springs from the shackle
which can lead to uncontrolled axle movement and swaying.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inaccurate Weight Ratings and Manufacturer Negligence
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate weight ratings and manufacturer negligence can lead to unsafe towing conditions, accidents, and potentially catastrophic consequences, including damage to the vehicle and harm to occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Incorrect OEM information on UVW and GVWR stickers
failure to address frame flex and suspension issues
and inadequate attempts to rectify the problems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Frame flexing or failure can cause damage to the interior walls, cabinets, and countertops, and potentially lead to catastrophic failure while traveling, putting lives at risk.
symptoms: damage to interior walls and cabinets
countertop and cabinet rubbing against the walls
tears in the metal of the subframe
laminate flooring lifting and separating from the plywood underneath

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Frame Flex/Failure due to Broken Welds
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Frame flex or failure can cause interior and exterior damage to the RV, potentially leading to accidents or injuries while towing. It can also lead to costly repairs and extended downtime.
symptoms: interior and exterior damage to the RV
